    <h1>Airports &amp; Borders</h1>
    <p class="lede">Airports and border crossings are legally distinct from other locations. CBP officers have broader authority to stop, question, and search travelers than police have during a routine street encounter. You still have rights.</p>
    <p class="updated">Updated as of April 30, 2026</p>
  </div>
